WEBVTT

00:00:00.960 --> 00:00:05.360
Data science teams work in diverse technical environments with many data sources,

00:00:05.360 --> 00:00:10.560
coding tools, computational requirements, and client expectations for data products.

00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:16.400
Having this work spread across multiple systems creates inefficient work silos

00:00:16.400 --> 00:00:18.959
and introduces critical gaps in security.

00:00:21.040 --> 00:00:27.280
Our studio Workbench addresses all of this by providing IT the ability to manage and scale

00:00:27.280 --> 00:00:34.320
data ingestion, analysis, and data product creation securely, all from one place,

00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:39.200
while providing data scientists the ability to collaborate on R and Python projects,

00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:44.799
whether RStudio with its ability to run multiple versions of R in different sessions,

00:00:44.799 --> 00:00:51.599
or JupyterLab, or Jupyter Notebooks, or VS Code, each with the option of running pre-configured

00:00:51.599 --> 00:00:56.959
data connectors, requesting compute resources, and providing the ability to collaborate with

00:00:56.959 --> 00:01:03.200
in a shared environment. If they choose to use the RStudio IDE, team members can share projects

00:01:03.200 --> 00:01:08.800
and track work in real time, helping to keep up with changes and supporting best practices for

00:01:08.800 --> 00:01:14.400
code review, which ultimately allows data science leaders to build happy and effective teams while

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:19.839
delivering value to their stakeholders. Using RStudio Workbench, the data science team can

00:01:19.839 --> 00:01:25.199
create reports, dashboards, and interactive applications for their organization's decision

00:01:25.199 --> 00:01:31.919
makers, which can be hosted on platforms such as RStudio Connect. By moving work from the local

00:01:31.919 --> 00:01:36.959
laptop and onto RStudio Workbench, users can quickly authenticate and spin up the coding

00:01:36.959 --> 00:01:42.879
environment of their choice for either R or Python, providing easy access to pre-configured

00:01:42.879 --> 00:01:51.599
data connectors like Snowflake, MongoDB, and Spark, just to name a few. Your team can also request

00:01:51.599 --> 00:01:56.800
critical compute resources that they won't likely have access to on local systems, with different

00:01:56.800 --> 00:02:04.400
user or group profiles for default and max resource usage, which helps to control cost. RStudio Workbench

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:10.000
makes it easier for teams to work together by providing a standardized set of installed software,

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:14.559
which helps ensure that data science work is reproducible between team members,

00:02:14.559 --> 00:02:20.080
and integration with Git supports collaboration and code governance across coding environments.

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:31.440
RStudio Workbench. Enable your team to build great data science products.

